property.name: objectExportOptions
property.shortdesc: Export options for the object

property.name: transparencySettings
property.shortdesc: Transparency settings.

property.name: strokeTransparencySettings
property.shortdesc: Transparency settings for the stroke.

property.name: fillTransparencySettings
property.shortdesc: Transparency settings for the fill applied to the ObjectStyle.

property.name: contentTransparencySettings
property.shortdesc: Transparency settings for the content of the ObjectStyle.

property.name: objectEffectsEnablingSettings
property.shortdesc: The object effects enabling settings.

property.name: strokeEffectsEnablingSettings
property.shortdesc: The stroke effects enabling settings.

property.name: fillEffectsEnablingSettings
property.shortdesc: The fill effects enabling settings.

property.name: contentEffectsEnablingSettings
property.shortdesc: The content effects enabling settings.

property.name: id
property.shortdesc: The unique ID of the ObjectStyle.

property.name: isValid
property.shortdesc: Returns true if the object specifier resolves to valid objects.

property.name: parent
property.shortdesc: The parent of the ObjectStyle &#40;a Document, Application or ObjectStyleGroup).

property.name: index
property.shortdesc: The index of the ObjectStyle within its containing object.

property.name: events
property.shortdesc: A collection of events.

property.name: eventListeners
property.shortdesc: A collection of event listeners.

property.name: objectStyleExportTagMaps
property.shortdesc: A collection of object style export tag maps.

property.name: preferences
property.shortdesc: A collection of preferences objects.

property.name: enableTextFrameAutoSizingOptions
property.shortdesc: If true, the object style will apply auto-sizing text frame options.

property.name: enableExportTagging
property.shortdesc: If true, the object style will apply an epub tag and class.

property.name: enableObjectExportAltTextOptions
property.shortdesc: If true, the object style will apply alt text export options.

property.name: enableObjectExportTaggedPdfOptions
property.shortdesc: If true, the object style will apply tagged pdf export options.

property.name: enableObjectExportEpubOptions
property.shortdesc: If true, the object style will apply epub export options.

property.name: basedOn
property.shortdesc: The style that this style is based on. Can return: ObjectStyle or String.

property.name: name
property.shortdesc: The name of the ObjectStyle.

property.name: appliedParagraphStyle
property.shortdesc: The paragraph style applied to the text. Can also accept: String.

property.name: applyNextParagraphStyle
property.shortdesc: If true, applies paragraph styles using Next Paragraph Style settings, beginning with the Next Paragraph Style defined in the paragraph style associated with the object style &#40;if any).

property.name: enableFill
property.shortdesc: If true, the object style will apply a fill.

property.name: enableStroke
property.shortdesc: If true, the object style will apply a stroke.

property.name: enableParagraphStyle
property.shortdesc: If true, the object style will apply a paragraph style.

property.name: enableTextFrameGeneralOptions
property.shortdesc: If true, the object style will apply general text frame options.

property.name: enableTextFrameBaselineOptions
property.shortdesc: If true, the object style will apply baseline text frame options.

property.name: enableStoryOptions
property.shortdesc: If true, the object style will apply story options.

property.name: enableTextWrapAndOthers
property.shortdesc: If true, the object style will apply text wrap, contour, and non-printing settings.

property.name: enableAnchoredObjectOptions
property.shortdesc: If true, the object style will apply an anchored object setting.

property.name: fillColor
property.shortdesc: The swatch &#40;color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the fill of the ObjectStyle. . Can also accept: String.

property.name: fillTint
property.shortdesc: The percent of tint to use in the ObjectStyle's fill color. &#40;To specify a tint percent, use a number in the range of 0 to 100; to use the inherited or overridden value, use -1.)

property.name: overprintFill
property.shortdesc: If true, the ObjectStyle's fill color overprints any underlying objects. If false, the fill color knocks out the underlying colors.

property.name: strokeWeight
property.shortdesc: The weight &#40;in points) to apply to the ObjectStyle's stroke.

property.name: miterLimit
property.shortdesc: The limit of the ratio of stroke width to miter length before a miter &#40;pointed) join becomes a bevel (squared-off) join.

property.name: endCap
property.shortdesc: The end shape of an open path.

property.name: endJoin
property.shortdesc: The corner join applied to the ObjectStyle.

property.name: strokeType
property.shortdesc: The name of the stroke style to apply. Can also accept: String.

property.name: leftLineEnd
property.shortdesc: The arrowhead applied to the start of the path.

property.name: rightLineEnd
property.shortdesc: The arrowhead applied to the end of the path.

property.name: strokeColor
property.shortdesc: The swatch &#40;color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the stroke of the ObjectStyle. Can also accept: String.

property.name: strokeTint
property.shortdesc: The percent of tint to use in object's stroke color. &#40;To specify a tint percent, use a number in the range of 0 to 100; to use the inherited or overridden value, use -1.)

property.name: overprintStroke
property.shortdesc: If true, the ObjectStyle's stroke color overprints any underlying objects. If false, the stroke color knocks out the  underlying colors.

property.name: gapColor
property.shortdesc: The swatch &#40;color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the gap of a dashed, dotted, or striped stroke. For information, see stroke type.

property.name: gapTint
property.shortdesc: The tint as a percentage of the gap color. &#40;To specify a tint percent, use a number in the range of 0 to 100; to use the inherited or overridden value, use -1.)

property.name: overprintGap
property.shortdesc: If true, the gap color overprints any underlying colors. If false, the gap color knocks out the underlying colors.

property.name: strokeAlignment
property.shortdesc: The stroke alignment applied to the ObjectStyle.

property.name: nonprinting
property.shortdesc: If true, the ObjectStyle does not print.

property.name: gradientFillAngle
property.shortdesc: The angle of a linear gradient applied to the fill of the ObjectStyle. &#40;Range: -180 to 180)

property.name: gradientStrokeAngle
property.shortdesc: The angle of a linear gradient applied to the stroke of the ObjectStyle. &#40;Range: -180 to 180)

property.name: textFramePreferences
property.shortdesc: Text frame preference settings.

property.name: baselineFrameGridOptions
property.shortdesc: Baseline frame grid option settings.

property.name: anchoredObjectSettings
property.shortdesc: Anchored object settings.

property.name: textWrapPreferences
property.shortdesc: The text wrap preference properties that define the default formatting for wrapping text around objects.

property.name: storyPreferences
property.shortdesc: Story preference settings.

property.name: topLeftCornerOption
property.shortdesc: The shape to be applied to the top left corner of rectangular shapes and all corners of non-rectangular shapes.Note: corner option differs from end join in which you can set a radius for a corner option, whereas the rounded or beveled effect of an end join depends on the stroke weight.

property.name: topRightCornerOption
property.shortdesc: The shape to apply to the top right corner of rectangular shapes

property.name: bottomLeftCornerOption
property.shortdesc: The shape to apply to the bottom left corner of rectangular shapes.

property.name: bottomRightCornerOption
property.shortdesc: The shape to apply to the bottom right corner of rectangular shapes.

property.name: topLeftCornerRadius
property.shortdesc: The radius in measurement units of the corner effect applied to the top left corner of rectangular shapes and all corners of non-rectangular shapes

property.name: topRightCornerRadius
property.shortdesc: The radius in measurement units of the corner effect applied to the top right corner of rectangular shapes

property.name: bottomLeftCornerRadius
property.shortdesc: The radius in measurement units of the corner effect applied to the bottom left corner of rectangular shapes

property.name: bottomRightCornerRadius
property.shortdesc: The radius in measurement units of the corner effect applied to the bottom right corner of rectangular shapes

property.name: frameFittingOptions
property.shortdesc: The frame fitting option to apply to placed or pasted content. Can be applied to a frame, object style, or document or to the application.

property.name: enableFrameFittingOptions
property.shortdesc: If true, the object style will apply frame fitting options.

property.name: enableStrokeAndCornerOptions
property.shortdesc: If true, the object style will apply stroke options and corner options.

property.name: label
property.shortdesc: A property that can be set to any string.

property.name: properties
property.shortdesc: A property that allows setting of several properties at the same time.

method.name: move
method.shortdesc: Moves the ObjectStyle to the specified location.

parameter.name: to
parameter.shortdesc: The new location relative to the reference object or within the container object.

parameter.name: reference
parameter.shortdesc: The reference object. Note: Required when the to parameter is before or after. Can accept: ObjectStyle, ObjectStyleGroup, Document or Application. &#40;Optional)

parameter.name: replacingWith
parameter.shortdesc: The style to apply in place of the deleted style. &#40;Optional)

method.name: insertLabel
method.shortdesc: Sets the label to the value associated with the specified key.

method.name: extractLabel
method.shortdesc: Gets the label value associated with the specified key.

method.name: toSource
method.shortdesc: Generates a string which, if executed, will return the ObjectStyle.

method.name: getElements
method.shortdesc: Resolves the object specifier, creating an array of object references.

parameter.name: handler
parameter.shortdesc: The event handler. Can accept: File or JavaScript Function.

parameter.name: handler
parameter.shortdesc: The registered event handler. Can accept: File or JavaScript Function.
